               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Valad'nāmah by Sulṭān Valad</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002005579 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002009961" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1263-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian, Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21899">Valad'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21899">ولد نامه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Early and rare copy of the lengthy Sufi treatise in mas̲navī form by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658613.0x000001 viaf_66900471" role="aut">Mawlavī Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad known as Sulṭān Valad</persName> (d. 761/1360), the founder of the <orgName>Mevlevi (Mawlavī) Sufi Order</orgName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>According to the brief opening prose preface (f. 1v), the author composed this work in imitation of his father <persName key="viaf_98930150" role="ant">Mawlavī Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad Balkhī Rūmī</persName>’s <title key="work_21899">Mas̲navī-yi maʿnavī</title> at the request of companions. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon, damaged (f. 104r): completed by (obliterated), 697/1298. 
Probably completed in <placeName>Konya</placeName>, <placeName>Seljuk Anatolia</placeName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Combinations of Arabic and Persian annotations on opening flyleaves. 
</p>
                        <p>Seals and inscriptions by later owners at beginning and end. 
</p>
                        <p>Squat and rounded cursive naskh with tawqīʿ/taʿlīq-style ligatures, arranged in four columns. 
</p>
                        <p>Rubrication. 
</p>
                        <p>Rulings in brown ink. 
</p>
                        <p>IOL red leather binding, stamp dated 16 Mar 1936. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios mounted on guards. 
</p>
                        <p>Opening and end defaced by water stains, smudging, fading, and excessive wormholes, with later repairs. Excessively cropped. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition poor. 
</p>
                     </note>
